         "id": "SECTION_steps",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### A next step\n\nOur understanding of multiplication has been evolving throughout the texts and applications published on History Tracers. So far, we have followed these steps:\n- We learned that multiplication is the repeated addition of the same number (<htcite0>).\n- We reinforced the idea of complementing a number by, whenever necessary, moving that value to the next decimal place (<htcite1>).\n- In the previous game, we advanced from multiplying a single-digit number by another to multiplying a number with tens and units by a single-digit number (<htcite2>).\n\nOur next step on this learning path will be to multiply numbers with more than two digits (units, tens, hundreds, etc.) by a single number. Given this scenario, reflect on the following question:",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "eaa59295-fb80-4c33-b1e4-bcdf3c11dabf",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "Adding the same number",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2025",
                        "month": "5",
                        "day": "9"
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "a1da73b2-5d6a-4343-98e9-2d9be753b123",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "Multiplying with Soroban and Suanpan (算盤)",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2026",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "5edb2a2d-ea6e-47dc-b526-e9db86c06181",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "Soroban and Suanpan (算盤): multiplication in practice",
                     "date_time": {
