                     }
                  }
               ],
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><center><div class=\"first_steps_reflection_parent\"><div class=\"first_steps_reflection question_mark\"><i class=\"fa-solid fa-brain\"></i></div><div class=\"first_steps_reflection\"><b>Reflection 1: Next step</b><br /><br />With everything that has been seen so far, how would you multiply a number with three, four, or even eight digits by another number?</div></div></center></p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "With everything we have seen so far, we can conclude that we should follow exactly the same steps we performed earlier, but repeating them more times.\n\nTo better visualize these new steps, we will again use the abacuses developed in China (Zhongguo, 中國) and Japan (Nippon-koku or Nihon-koku, 日本国).",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
